<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-01-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="637" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d637">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/18974:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Dublin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-27">January 27, 1942</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                    January 27—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5. Landing American troops port in Northern Ireland was broadcast
                                yesterday from London 9 p.m., from Dublin 10:10 p.m. This morning’s
                                Dublin papers display news briefly stating several thousand American
                                combat troops with artillery landed yesterday. Thus far no editorial
                                comment.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gray</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>